<div id="review_169727626" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/169727626" />
    <a title="Denise" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/4630364-denise"><img alt="Denise" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/f_50x66-6a03a5c12233c941481992b82eea8d23.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/169727626?book_show_action=true">May 20, 2011</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Denise" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Denise" href="/user/show/4630364-denise">Denise</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer169727626" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer13725104028001186387">The Mark of the Lion series is my favorite set of books by any auther...EVER. Francine Rivers made me a lifelong fan. I have read nearly every book she&apos;s written, and have KEPT THEM. In fact, I have loaned them out, not gotten them back, and repurchased them just so they&apos;d be on my bookshelves. The first two books of this series are the best fiction books I&apos;ve ever read. Period. <br/><br/>I love Hadasseh&apos;s beginnings...daughter of a man Jesus raised from the dead, from a devout family who are killed by th</span>
  <span id="freeText13725104028001186387" style="display:none">The Mark of the Lion series is my favorite set of books by any auther...EVER. Francine Rivers made me a lifelong fan. I have read nearly every book she's written, and have KEPT THEM. In fact, I have loaned them out, not gotten them back, and repurchased them just so they'd be on my bookshelves. The first two books of this series are the best fiction books I've ever read. Period. <br /><br />I love Hadasseh's beginnings...daughter of a man Jesus raised from the dead, from a devout family who are killed by the Romans in AD 70, with Hadassah being their only survivor (and the family member with the weakest faith), taken as a slave to Ephesus and becoming servant to Marcus Valerian's wealthy, godless family. The characters are breathtaking. Hadassah begins as a frightened, weak, abandoned Jewess who has a thread of faith in Jesus. Through the pages of her story, we see a young woman whose love, tenacity, courage and faith stand in front of the powerful, influential, indulged Valerian family. They are changed forever because of the waif who entered their house with a shaved head and downcast eyes, but with the capacity to love and serve them...and to teach them of life's true riches.<br /><br />Do you think we live luxuriously today? Do you think, as I did, that first century Rome would be archaic in comparison? I was shocked at their plenty, at their modern luxuries and appetites. The graphic violence and behavior of these people was not at all what I expected. Truly, there is nothing new under the sun. <br /><br />Miss Rivers did a phenomenal job here in describing ancient Rome (and Ephesus). There is a subplot in this first book with Atretes, the gladiator. Unimaginable life. It was fascinating and heartbreaking. She didn't spare us the reality.<br /><br />This is an epic series that is absolutely profound. Never have I experienced such deep, vulnerable characters that I grew to love so much that I practially mourned when I finished the books. Masterful, masterful writing. I read these books years ago (multiple times, in fact), and I have to say....nothing else has ever compared. If you have not read this series, I can't recommend it highly enough. I believe men will enjoy them as much as women will. I actually enjoyed the first two books more than the third. But they are my most treasured books. Five stars aren't enough. </span>
  <a data-text-id="13725104028001186387" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


